Destruction or threats to 70 percent of the coral reefs represent a sharp rise from 59 percent in the last study in 2002.
After global warming _ blamed for higher water temperatures and carbon dioxide concentrations _ threats to the reefs include coral disease, coastal development and pollution runoff from land-based sources.
